The paper discusses a meta-learning model based on Recurrent Neural Networks, which is closely connected to variational inference and the Minimum Description Length principle. These topics are commonly associated with the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also investigates human decision-making, which falls under the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper uses a resource-bounded objective, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
